	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />cool demo.  i thought about 4011 streaming with other tasks crammed in between a little while back, you get a decent chunk of time with 8khz or 16khz between 4011 writes.  i thought about using irq to time between 4011 but then i remembered ppu address lines aren't active in nmi so that wouldn't work out too well.
<br />
<br />eventually i'd like to write a pcm streamer but i'd also want it doing something in the background otherwise it's pretty unremarkable.  i co-authored <a href="http://www.sendspace.com/file/tpv76d" class="postlink">something similar</a> for the snes, was pretty fun to make.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


